#week-title("Three", "Moon in Signs & The Solar Cycle")

=== Core Teaching

Beyond the lunar phase, the *zodiacal sign* in which the Moon resides influences
the Work. In the vegetable kingdom:
- *Earth signs:* Best for root work.
- *Water signs:* Best for leaf and succulent work.
- *Air signs:* Best for flowers.
- *Fire signs:* Best for seeds and fruit.

The *Solar Cycle* (Solstices and Equinoxes) also governs the strength of the
universal seed as it descends into the atmosphere. Learning to move with these
rhythms rather than against them distinguishes the alchemist from the chemist.

=== Topics This Week

- The four elements in the Zodiac
- Moon in signs: practical advice for gathering and processing
- The solar cycle and its impact on long extractions

#inner-work[
  *The Daily Single-Card Practice*

  Begin a daily single-card practice. Each morning, draw one card from the full
  78-card deck. Do not seek a "reading" or prediction. Simply hold the card and
  observe its imagery.

  Record the card in your Tarot journal. At the end of the day, look back and
  see how the card's energy relates to the events or internal moods of the day.
  This builds your intuitive link to the archetypes.
]

